SIMPLE: counter-roll
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Counter-roll
<hw>Coun"ter-roll`</hw> <pr>(-r?l`)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Cf.
<er>Control</er>.]</ety> <fld>(O. Eng. Law)</fld> <def>A duplicate roll
(record or account) kept by an officer as a check upon another officer's
roll.</def> <rj><au>Burrill.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><note>⟦hand⟧ As a verb this word is contracted into
<xex>control</xex>. See <er>Control</er>.</note>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Counterrolment</ent>⟦br⟧
